<TITLE> ACC sues Suja, wife </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 10 (bdnews24.com)- The Anticorruption Commission Tuesday filed a corruption case against former Awami League whip Mostafa Rashidi Suja. Suja's wife Khoteja Rashidi and their two daughters Sanjida Rashidi and Tanija Rashidi have also been accused in the case, filed by deputy director for the ACC Moniruzzaman Khan with Ramna Police Station. Assistant sub inspector Didar Hossain told bdnews24.com that the case accuses Suja of earning Tk 4.4 crore outside their legal income. ACC officials will soon begin investigations into the case. bdnews24.c
